WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.250 --> 00:00:02.550
&gt;&gt; Rob Casper: Welcome.

00:00:02.550 --> 00:00:04.490
Good morning.

00:00:04.490 --> 00:00:07.370
Welcome to the National
Book Festival.

00:00:07.370 --> 00:00:10.120
My name is Rob Casper.

00:00:10.120 --> 00:00:13.850
I'm the head of the Poetry and
Literature Center at the Library

00:00:13.850 --> 00:00:16.410
of Congress and we're
thrilled to have you

00:00:16.410 --> 00:00:20.670
for this panel celebrating
new poets of Native Nations.

00:00:20.670 --> 00:00:23.500
I should say it's both
a panel and a reading,

00:00:23.500 --> 00:00:26.370
so you'll hear all
sorts of poems

00:00:26.370 --> 00:00:28.980
in the next hour and 15 minutes.

00:00:28.980 --> 00:00:32.690
We'll have a great wonderful
conversation up on stage,

00:00:32.690 --> 00:00:36.020
and you'll have the
opportunity to ask questions.

00:00:36.020 --> 00:00:40.780
There should be mics on either
side that you can step up to.

00:00:40.780 --> 00:00:43.220
When we get to that
point I'll redirect you

00:00:43.220 --> 00:00:46.700
so we can make sure that works.

00:00:46.700 --> 00:00:48.200
All day here at the Library

00:00:48.200 --> 00:00:50.820
of Congress National Book
Festival we are recognizing

00:00:50.820 --> 00:00:53.320
and celebrating the
importance of reading

00:00:53.320 --> 00:00:55.570
and authors and books.

00:00:55.570 --> 00:00:59.470
The Library of Congress makes it
seem easy to do this every year,

00:00:59.470 --> 00:01:02.170
but the truth is the National
Book Festival is a huge

00:01:02.170 --> 00:01:06.610
undertaking, is a huge financial
undertaking, and it is free

00:01:06.610 --> 00:01:09.080
for everyone because
of the generous support

00:01:09.080 --> 00:01:11.510
from our sponsors
and supporters.

00:01:11.510 --> 00:01:12.810
One of our great sponsors

00:01:12.810 --> 00:01:15.130
and supporters is the
National Endowment for the Arts

00:01:15.130 --> 00:01:19.050
which makes this poetry and
prose pavilion possible.

00:01:19.050 --> 00:01:22.120
You should find out about the
National Endowment for the Arts.

00:01:22.120 --> 00:01:24.210
The staff from the Literature
Division is in the back.

00:01:24.210 --> 00:01:26.230
They have materials
you can check out.

00:01:26.230 --> 00:01:29.370
They are a great supporter
of poets and writers

00:01:29.370 --> 00:01:33.700
in this country and have been
doing so for a good long time.

00:01:33.700 --> 00:01:36.860
You can also spread the joy
of reading with a gift online

00:01:36.860 --> 00:01:41.460
at loc.gov/donate
from the festival app

00:01:41.460 --> 00:01:44.560
or when you purchase
books today.

00:01:44.560 --> 00:01:48.010
So let me tell you about
this panel in reading.

00:01:48.010 --> 00:01:50.740
We have a good amount
of time today to get

00:01:50.740 --> 00:01:52.110
into a great conversation.

00:01:52.110 --> 00:01:57.500
And I'm thrilled to have two
wonderful poets including my

00:01:57.500 --> 00:01:59.590
good friend Heid Erdrich.

00:01:59.590 --> 00:02:02.500
I've had many conversations
with Heid over the years

00:02:02.500 --> 00:02:05.110
about new poets of
Native Nations and I want

00:02:05.110 --> 00:02:07.330
to say how honored
I am personally

00:02:07.330 --> 00:02:09.370
to be part of its launch.

00:02:09.370 --> 00:02:13.560
Special thanks also to Graywolf
Press and Editor Jeff Shotts

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:16.790
for supporting this panel.

00:02:16.790 --> 00:02:19.620
We were supposed to
have a third panelist

00:02:19.620 --> 00:02:21.060
and reader, Natalie Diaz.

00:02:21.060 --> 00:02:22.360
She is in transit.

00:02:22.360 --> 00:02:25.820
We're hoping she makes it, so
we're just going to kick off

00:02:25.820 --> 00:02:28.650
and then we'll see what happens.

00:02:28.650 --> 00:02:32.000
Let me tell you a little
bit about this event.

00:02:32.000 --> 00:02:36.040
Our other poet, Jennifer
Foerster, will read her poems

00:02:36.040 --> 00:02:40.540
from the anthology, then
Heid will talk a little bit

00:02:40.540 --> 00:02:44.250
about the anthology and read
poems by other contributors.

00:02:44.250 --> 00:02:47.630
Then she'll invite Jennifer to
